geneVariantDescriptions.description: CCNE1 over exp indicates an over expression of the Ccne1 protein. However, the mechanism causing the over expression is unspecified.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Roscovotine (seliciclib) induced apoptosis and inhibited growth of CCNE1 (cyclin E)-dependent murine lung cancer cell lines in culture, and demonstrated anti-tumor activity in mouse models (PMID: 20028770).

references.title: Targeting the cyclin E-Cdk-2 complex represses lung cancer growth by triggering anaphase catastrophe.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Roscovitine (seliciclib), in combination with Alvocidib (flavopiridol) inhibited growth in multiple myeloma cells over expressing CCNE1 (PMID: 22558078).

references.title: Characterization of cyclin E expression in multiple myeloma and its functional role in seliciclib-induced apoptotic cell death.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, the combination of Ibrance (palbociclib) and AZD0855 acted synergistically to decrease proliferation of pancreatic cancer cell lines with loss of CDKN2A and upregulation of CCNE1 and CCND1 in culture (PMID: 25156567).
